== 早年经历和教育 ==

=== 家族传承 ===
[[File:McCainFatherandGrandfather.jpg|thumb]]内的一艘美国海军舰船上。]]

1936年8月29日，约翰·西德尼·麦凯恩三世<ref name="bioguide">{{cite web | publisher = United States Congress | url = http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=m000303 | title = McCain, John Sidney, III, (1936 - ) | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160105090911/http://bioguide.congress.gov/scripts/biodisplay.pl?index=m000303 | accessdate = 2016-01-08 | work = Biographical Directory of the United States Congress | archivedate = 2016-01-05 | deadurl = no}}</ref>生于[[巴拿马|巴拿马]][[巴拿马运河区|运河区]][[可可索罗|可可索罗海军航空站]]<ref>{{cite news | last = Liptak | first = Adam | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/11/us/politics/11mccain.html | title = A Hint of New Life to a McCain Birth Issue | newspaper = The New York Times | date = 2008-07-11 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151202005534/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/11/us/politics/11mccain.html | archivedate = 2015-12-02}}</ref><ref name="timberg-bio-ch1">{{cite book | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151128111344/http://www.nytimes.com/books/first/t/timberg-mccain.html | last = Timberg | first = Robert | title = John McCain: An American Odyssey | deadurl = no | publisher = Touchstone Books | year = 1999 | location = New York | isbn = 0-684-86794-X | pages = 17–34 | url = http://www.nytimes.com/books/first/t/timberg-mccain.html | archivedate = 2015-11-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/fact-checker/2008/05/citizen_mccain.html |title=The Fact Checker: Citizen McCain |last=Dobbs |first=Michael |publisher=''The Washington Post'' |date=2008-05-02 |accessdate=2016-01-08 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120707132854/http://blog.washingtonpost.com/fact-checker/2008/05/citizen_mccain.html |archivedate=2012-07-07 |deadurl=no }}</ref>的[[美国海军|海军]]医院<ref name="Alexander-2002">{{cite book | title = Man of the People: The Life of John McCain | url = https://archive.org/details/manofpeoplelifeo00alex | first = Paul | last = Alexander | isbn = 0-471-22829-X | publisher = John Wiley & Sons | location = Hoboken, New Jersey | year = 2002}}</ref>{{rp|12}}<ref>{{cite news | publisher = ''Panama American'' | date = 1936-08-31 | format = [[PDF|PDF]] | url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/documents/mccain_announcement_041708.pdf | title = Atlantic Side: Society Notes | accessdate = 2016-01-08 | archive-date = 2021-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210221060831/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/documents/mccain_announcement_041708.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/fact-checker/2008/05/john_mccains_birthplace.html |title=The Fact Checker: John McCain's Birthplace |last=Dobbs |first=Michael |publisher=''The Washington Post'' |date=2008-05-20 |accessdate=2016-01-08 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120716022656/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/fact-checker/2008/05/john_mccains_birthplace.html |archivedate=2012-07-16 |deadurl=no }}</ref>，他的父亲是海军军官[[小约翰·席德尼·麦凯恩|小约翰·“杰克”·麦凯恩]]，母亲叫[[罗伯塔·麦凯恩|罗伯塔·麦凯恩]]（{{lang|en|Roberta McCain}}，1912–2020），“莱特”（{{lang|en|Wright}}）是母亲的[[女性人名|娘家姓]]。麦凯恩三世有[[苏格兰－爱尔兰裔美国人|苏格兰混爱尔兰裔]]和[[英格兰裔美国人|英格兰裔]]血统<ref name="nehgs">{{cite web | last = Roberts | first = Gary Boyd | title = On the Ancestry, Royal Descent, and English and American Notable Kin of Senator John Sidney McCain IV | publisher = New England Historic Genealogical Society | url = http://www.newenglandancestors.org/research/services/56_ancestry_john_mccain.asp | accessdate = 2009-01-25 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090125161140/http://www.newenglandancestors.org/research/services/56_ancestry_john_mccain.asp | archivedate = 2009-01-25 | deadurl = yes}}</ref>。

麦凯恩三世的祖父母辈都是[[阿肯色州|阿肯色州]]、[[密西西比州|密西西比州]]和[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]]居民，而且大部分父系和母系先祖都是[[美国南部|南方人]]<ref name="nehgs" />。麦凯恩家族[[父系制度|父系]]祖居密西西比州[[卡洛尔县_(密西西比州)|卡洛尔县]]<ref name="salon021500">{{cite news | url = http://archive.salon.com/politics2000/feature/2000/02/15/mccain/ | title = McCain's ancestors owned slaves | last1 = Parker | first1 = Suzi | last2 = Tapper | first2 = Jake | publisher = ''Salon'' | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090429071111/http://archive.salon.com/politics2000/feature/2000/02/15/mccain/ | date = 2000-02-15 | accessdate = 2009-04-29 | archivedate = 2009-04-29 | deadurl = yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151106224053/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/03/31/mccain.tour/ | deadurl = no | url = http://edition.cnn.com/2008/POLITICS/03/31/mccain.tour/ | title = McCain tells his story to voters | publisher = CNN | date = 2008-03-31 | accessdate = 2016-01-08 | archivedate = 2015-11-06}}</ref>，从1848年起就在[[特奥克_(密西西比州)|特奥克]]（{{lang|en|Teoc}}）拥有面积达8.1平方公里的种植园，并且一直经营到1952年止<ref name="salon021500" /><ref name="McCain-Salter-1999">{{cite book | last1 = McCain | first1 = John | last2 = Salter | first2 = Mark | title = Faith of My Fathers | url = https://archive.org/details/faithofmyfathers00mcca | publisher = Random House | year = 1999 | location = New York | isbn = 0-375-50191-6}}</ref>{{rp|21}}。[[南北战争|南北战争]]爆发前，种植园内还有许多[[美国奴隶制度|奴隶]]，其中有些人的后裔也采用麦凯恩家族的姓氏，自称“[[麦凯恩黑人|麦凯恩黑人]]”（{{lang|en|black McCains}}）<ref>{{ cite news | last = Chideya | first = Farai | title = Black McCains Share Family's Struggles, Triumphs | publisher = NPR | url = http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=95937654&ft=1&f=1021 | date = 2008-10-21 | accessdate = 2016-01-08 | archivedate = 2014-10-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141006164722/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=95937654&ft=1&f=1021}}</ref>。内战结束后，[[佃农|佃农]]代替了原来的奴隶，蓝调歌手兼吉他手[[密西西比·约翰·赫特|密西西比·约翰·赫特]]（{{lang|en|Mississippi John Hurt}}）就是在麦凯恩家族的种植园出生，是麦凯恩黑人的后代<ref name="salon021500" />。

作为美国军事世家，麦凯恩家族的先辈曾参与[[北美印第安战争|北美印第安战争]]<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />、[[美国独立战争|美国独立战争]]（麦凯恩因此一直是[[美国革命之子|美国革命之子]]成员）<ref name="az-trivia">{{cite news | url = http://archive.azcentral.com/news/specials/mccain/articles/mccaintrivia-CR.html | title = McCain trivia | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130117215210/http://www.azcentral.com/news/specials/mccain/articles/mccaintrivia-CR.html?nclick_check=1 |publisher=''The Arizona Republic'' |date=2007-03-02 |deadurl=no |accessdate=2016-01-08 |archivedate=2013-01-17 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Perera |first=Srianthi |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120719142926/http://www.azcentral.com/community/chandler/articles/2010/02/28/20100228sar0225.html |title=Sons of the American Revolution aims to grow in Arizona |url=http://www.azcentral.com/community/chandler/articles/2010/02/28/20100228sar0225.html |newspaper=The Arizona Republic |date=2010-02-28 |accessdate=2016-01-09 |archivedate=2012-07-19 |deadurl=no }}</ref>、[[1812年战争|1812年战争]]<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|20}}，在内战期间为[[美利坚联盟国|美利坚联盟国]]效力<ref name="salon021500" />，还曾参与[[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />。麦凯恩家族中也有投机暴富分子。麦凯恩的外祖父阿奇博尔德·赖特（{{lang|en|Archibald Wright}}，1875至1971年）<ref name="wapo072208">{{cite news |title=McCain's Maverick Side: Grandpa Would Be Proud |last=Weisman |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/07/21/AR2008072102653.html |first=Jonathan |publisher=''[[华盛顿邮报|The Washington Post]]'' |date=2008-07-22 |accessdate=2016-01-09 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130205193525/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/07/21/AR2008072102653.html |archivedate=2013-02-05 |deadurl=no }}</ref>在密西西比州长大，但青年时就因面临多起赌博和无证经营指控逃到[[俄克拉何马州|俄克拉何马州]][[马斯科吉_(俄克拉何马州)|马斯科吉]]<ref name="wapo072208" />，然后通过建州早期的土地交易及在[[美国西南部|美国西南部]]开采原油发迹<ref name="wapo072208" /><ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|11}}。到40岁时，已经致富的赖特选择早早退休陪伴家人，从此再也没有工作过<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" /><ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|11}}。赖特的家人在俄克拉何马州和[[南加利福尼亚州|南加利福尼亚州]]生活，罗伯塔和双胞胎姐妹罗伊纳（{{lang|en|Rowena}}）都受爷爷影响成为毕生的旅行和历险爱好者<ref name="nyt121407">{{cite news | date = 2007-12-14 | accessdate = 2016-01-09 | deadurl = no | title = The Road Trip of 2 Lifetimes, and Still Going | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120407121604/http://travel.nytimes.com/2007/12/14/travel/escapes/14sisters.html | archivedate = 2012-04-07 | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/14/travel/escapes/14sisters.html?_r=0 | last = Orth | first = Maureen | publisher = ''[[纽约时报|The New York Times]]''}}</ref>。家族中还不乏特立独行之辈：阿奇博尔德的夫人默特尔（{{lang|en|Myrtle}}）反对罗伯塔同当时还只是水手的杰克·麦凯恩交往，结果两人选择私奔，并在墨西哥[[蒂华纳|蒂华纳]]的一间酒吧成婚<ref name="nw083008">{{cite news | url = http://www.newsweek.com/john-mccain-hidden-depths-88349 | title = Hidden Depths | last = Meacham | first = Jon | publisher = ''Newsweek'' | date = 2008-08-30 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160106043221/http://www.newsweek.com/john-mccain-hidden-depths-88349 | accessdate = 2016-01-09 | archivedate = 2016-01-06}}</ref>。

麦凯恩的爸爸和爷爷之后都成为海军上将，是美国历史上第一对官拜四星上将的父子<ref name="az-naval">{{cite news | url = http://www.azcentral.com/news/election/mccain/articles/2007/03/01/20070301mccainbio-chapter2.html | title = John McCain Report: At the Naval Academy | last1 = Nowicki | first1 = Dan | last2 = Muller | first2 = Bill | work = The Arizona Republic | date = 2007-03-01 | accessdate = 2016-01-10}} Part of multi-chapter biographical profile of John McCain.  Originally published by ''The Arizona Republic'' as "McCain: The life story of Arizona's maverick senator", written by reporter Bill Muller, 1999-10-03. Reporter Dan Nowicki updated and revised the biography with additional material in January 2007.  See [http://www.azcentral.com/news/specials/mccain/articles/0301mccainbio-postscript.html "How the biography was put together"] for background and bibliographic sources.</ref>。麦凯恩的爷爷老约翰·麦凯恩（{{lang|en|John S. "Slew" McCain, Sr.}}，1884至1945年）是[[航空母舰|航母]]作战先驱<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />，曾于1942年指挥[[瓜达尔卡纳尔岛战役|瓜达尔卡纳尔岛战役]]中美军的所有陆基空中作战支援和掩护，之后又在1944至1945年率领[[快速航母特遣舰队|快速航母特遣舰队]]积极投身[[第二次世界大战太平洋战场|第二次世界大战太平洋战场]]。他在[[菲律宾战役_(1944年至1945年)|菲律宾战役]]和[[冲绳岛战役|冲绳岛战役]]中指挥的作战行动，以及向[[中华民国|台湾]]和[[日本列岛|日本列岛]]发动的空袭，对战争接近尾声时的日本海军和空军构成毁灭性打击<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|13–14}}。老麦凯恩在[[降伏文书|东京湾的日本投降仪式]]过去仅4天后去世，是当时的头条新闻<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />。杰克·麦凯恩是二战期间美国在多个战场军事行动的潜艇舰长，曾获[[银星勋章|银星]]和[[铜星勋章|铜星勋章]]<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|13–14}}。

=== 早年经历 ===
[[File:Admiral_McCain,_wife,_and_sons.jpg|thumb]]
麦凯恩的家人叫他“约翰尼”（{{lang|en|Johnny}}）<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|12}}，他的姐姐桑迪（{{lang|en|Sandy}}）生于1934年，弟弟乔（{{lang|en|Joe}}）于1942年出世<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" /><ref name="nw083008" />，受父亲岗位调动的影响，一家人在约翰尼10岁前都经常搬家，辗转[[新伦敦_(康涅狄格州)|新伦敦]]、[[珍珠港|珍珠港]]，以及太平洋上的另外多个军事基地<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|19}}。麦凯恩的暑假有时会在位于特奥克的家族种植园度过<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|21}}，但他总觉得军旅生涯比种植园的生活更适合自己<ref name="salon021500" />。每当搬到一地，麦凯恩就会进入基地的已有学校就读<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|19}}，但由于学校课程未必符合他的需求，自己的上课时间也难以保障，所以这经常对他接受教育造成不利影响<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|19}}。1941年[[珍珠港事件|珍珠港事件]]爆发后，麦凯恩的父亲离开了很长一段时间<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />，孩子的教育则主要通过母亲的努力来实现。罗伯塔利用家族经常长途旅行的机遇带着孩子前去参观历史和文化遗迹<ref name="nyt121407" /><ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|101–103}}，麦凯恩之后回忆称，正是母亲让他的生命中有这么多快乐，即便遭遇不幸，他也不会失去快乐生活的希望<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|101–103}}。作为[[共和党_(美国)|共和党人]]，罗伯塔让孩子紧跟时事，不过受父亲的军旅生涯影响，一家人通常不会向外人透露家族党派立场<ref name="wapo030200">{{cite news | title = Out of the Fire, Politics Calls; Ex-POW Turns Washington Insider | last = Romano | first = Lois | publisher = ''The Washington Post'' | date = 2000-03-02}}</ref>。

二战结束后，麦凯恩的父亲继续在海军服役，有时还在政治联络职位工作<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />。一家定居[[北弗吉尼亚|北弗吉尼亚]]后，麦凯恩于1946至1949年间进入[[亚历山德里亚_(弗吉尼亚州)|亚历山德里亚]]的[[圣斯蒂芬和圣艾格尼丝学校|圣斯蒂芬学校]]就读，同之前的学校相比，该校教育质量更高<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|20}}。在家人眼里，麦凯恩一直安静、值得信赖而且懂礼貌<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" />，但就读圣斯蒂芬学校期间，他开始变得不守规矩、桀骜不驯<ref name="alextimes">{{cite news | archivedate = 2008-10-12 | deadurl = yes | last = Arundel | url= http://www.alextimes.com/article.asp?article=7851&paper=1&cat=141 | title = Episcopal fetes a favorite son | first = John | work = Alexandria Times | date = 2007-12-06 | accessdate = 2008-10-12 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081012094233/http://www.alextimes.com/article.asp?article=7851&paper=1&cat=141}}</ref>。接下来的两年，一家又跟随父亲前往其它海军基地度过<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|21}}，到青年时，麦凯恩一共就读过的学校约有20所<ref name="ap-wmd">{{cite news | title = McCain's WMD Is A Mouth That Won't Quit | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151106220527/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/politics/2007-11-03-998821539_x.htm | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/news/politics/2007-11-03-998821539_x.htm | agency = Associated Press | publisher = ''[[今日美国|USA Today]]'' | date = 2007-11-04 | accessdate = 2016-01-10 | first = Calvin | last = Woodward | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2015-11-06}}</ref>，经常因在学校打架而受纪律处分<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|100}}。据麦凯恩之后回忆，受父亲事业的影响，他经常需要同自己的朋友道别，这也是他童年时代最悲伤的回忆。每到一所新的学校，他就急于通过张狂的态度来结识新朋友，弥补失去之前老朋友的损失。所以他在每所新学校里都变得越来越以个人为中心，越来越倾向于制造麻烦。<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|107–108}}

1951年，麦凯恩进入亚历山德里亚的[[弗吉尼亚州亚历山德里亚圣公会高中|圣公会高中]]就读，该校为全男性私立寄宿学校，学术品质优异，生活环境朴素，有严格的[[学术荣誉守则|荣誉守则]]和捉弄新生的传统<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|22–24}}<ref name="wapo083108">{{cite news |title=A Turbulent Youth Under a Strong Father's Shadow |last=Leahy |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/08/30/AR2008083001786_pf.html |first=Michael |publisher=''The Washington Post'' |date=2008-08-31 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121210043006/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/08/30/AR2008083001786_pf.html |accessdate=2016-01-10 |deadurl=no |archivedate=2012-12-10 }}</ref>。校内大部分学子都是南方富有人家子弟，麦凯恩由此见识到海军文化以外的生活和事业<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|108–110}}<ref name="Timberg-1999">{{cite book | last = Timberg | first = Robert | title = John McCain: An American Odyssey | url = https://archive.org/details/johnmccainameric00timb | publisher = Touchstone Books | year = 1999 | location = New York | isbn = 0-684-86794-X}}</ref>{{rp|23–24}}。其它同学给个性好斗而火爆的麦凯恩起的绰号包括“朋克”和“麦坏坏”（{{lang|en|McNasty}}），他对自己的硬汉形象也很满意并继续发场光大，还结交了几个朋友<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" /><ref name="alextimes" /><ref name="vf0207">{{cite news | url = http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/02/mccain200702 | title = Prisoner of Conscience | last = Purdum | first = Todd S | publisher = ''[[名利场_(杂志)|Vanity Fair]]'' | date = 2007-02 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150120054149/http://www.vanityfair.com/politics/features/2007/02/mccain200702 | accessdate = 2015-01-20 | archivedate = 2015-01-20 | deadurl = yes}}</ref><ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|28}}。麦凯恩曾两次在[[中学摔跤|摔跤比赛]]中获[[校队奖章|校队奖章]]，在[[摔跤重量分级|轻量级]]比赛中表现优异<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|25–26}}。他还在中学[[美式足球|足球]]和网球校队效力，参与学生报纸和年鉴编制，并投身话剧社<ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|26}}。语文老师兼足球教练[[威廉·毕·罗芙奥三世|威廉·毕·罗芙奥三世]]（{{lang|en|William Bee Ravenel III}}）对麦凯恩的学习、荣誉和自我形象意识有很大影响<ref>{{cite news | accessdate = 2016-01-10 | url = http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Vote2008/Story?id=4565619 | title = McCain the 'Punk' Goes Back to School | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130324093922/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/Vote2008/story?id=4565619 | deadurl = no | author = Ed O'Keefe | publisher = ABC News | date = 2008-04-01 | archivedate = 2013-03-24}} Ravenel was the only person outside McCain's family whom he sought out to talk with upon his return from being a POW in Vietnam, but Ravenel had died two years earlier.</ref>。麦凯恩之后表示，自己的学术表现“平凡无奇，但还能接受”<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|116}}，他在1954年高中毕业<ref name="alextimes" />。

=== 海军学院 ===
[[File:McCain_at_Annapolis.JPG|thumb]]的约翰·麦凯恩，摄于20世纪50年代中期。]]
1954年6月，在入学考试中表现不凡的麦凯恩得以跟随父亲和爷爷的脚步，进入[[安那波利斯|安那波利斯]]的[[安纳波利斯海军学院|美国海军学院]]深造<ref name="timberg-bio-ch1" /><ref name="timberg-ns-ch1">{{cite book | last = Timberg | first = Robert | title = The Nightingale's Song | url = https://archive.org/details/nightingalessong00timb | publisher = Simon & Schuster | year = 1996 | location = New York | isbn = 0-684-80301-1}}</ref>{{rp|31–35}}。据麦凯恩回忆，当年他只是觉得进入海军学院是无可避免的，所以没有做任何反抗地接收宿命，以此来看，当年应该是父母强令他前去该校，没有任何商量余地<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|110–111}}<ref name="Timberg-1999" />{{rp|34}}。

麦凯恩对在海军学院学习感到矛盾<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}，所以有意违反学校的一些规矩和传统<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|120–124}}。每年他被记过上百次，成为违规“世纪俱乐部”的一员<ref name="az-naval" />，记过的原因包括鞋子擦得不亮、[[阅兵|编队]]失误、房间凌乱和说话出格等<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}，父亲为此多次来校训斥他<ref name="wapo083108" />。麦凯恩很讨厌“新生年”，刚刚进入学院的新生会在这年遭受各种严酷考验和捉弄，整个班的学生会因此减少四分之一<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|24–29}}。对于那些级别更高的人随意动用权力强迫他屈服的做法，麦凯恩非常反感：“什么玩意儿，我真恨透了这些狗屁”<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}，如果看到这些人对他人故伎重演，麦凯恩还经常插手干预<ref name="az-naval" /><ref name="wapo083108" />。麦凯恩这时身高只有1米7<ref name="az-trivia" />，体重58公斤<ref name="nw051407" />，虽然技能不佳，但凭借无畏且勇往直前“没有倒车档”的品性，他还是在学院[[轻量级拳击手|轻量拳击]]队中打了3年<ref name="nw051407">{{cite news | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090625230822/http://www.newsweek.com/id/34694 | archivedate = 2009-06-25 | url = http://www.newsweek.com/can-mccain-box-his-way-nomination-101607 | title = John McCain: 'I Learned How to Take Hard Blows' | last = Bailey | first = Holly | publisher = ''Newsweek'' | date = 2007-05-14 | accessdate = 2016-01-10}}</ref>。在该校就读的最后一年里，麦凯恩率领营级拳击队拿下全旅冠军<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|141}}。

麦凯恩天资聪颖，1984年的测试结果表明他的[[智商|智商]]达到133<ref>{{cite news|archivedate=2015-09-19 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150919133908/http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0%2C9171%2C992860%2C00.html |deadurl=no |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,992860,00.html |title=The Diagnosis: "Stable" |last=Carney |first=James |publisher=''[[时代_(杂志)|Time]]'' |date=1999-12-13 |accessdate=2016-01-10 }}</ref><ref name="Alexander-2002" />{{rp|207}}，所以在感兴趣的几个科目，如英语文学、历史和政府上表现优异<ref name="az-naval" /><ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}。海军学院的所有学生都必须学习固定的[[理学士|理学士]]课程<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.usna.edu/VirtualTour/150years/ | title = A Brief History of the United States Naval Academy | publisher = United States Naval Academy | accessdate = 2012-10-10 | archivedate = 2012-10-10 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121010083245/http://www.usna.edu///VirtualTour/150years/}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | first = Lieutenant Colonel Joseph J. | last = Blum | date = 1977-05-06 | title = Changing Educational Goals at the United States Naval Academy | journal = Air University Review | volume = 28 | issue = 4 | pages = 72–82 | archivedate = 2013-02-19 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130219011107/http://www.airpower.au.af.mil/airchronicles/aureview/1977/may-jun/blum.html | url = http://www.airpower.au.af.mil/airchronicles/aureview/1977/may-jun/blum.html | accessdate = 2013-02-19 | deadurl = yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/21/magazine/21WWLN-McCain-t.html |title=What a Naval Officer Now Knows |last=Traub |first=James |publisher=''The New York Times Magazine'' |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706182205/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/21/magazine/21WWLN-McCain-t.html |date=2008-09-19 |accessdate=2016-01-10 |archivedate=2015-07-06 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>，许多同学对他在数学、科学和工程类课程上临时抱佛脚的能力留下深刻印象<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|41–42}}。不过由于偏科严重，麦凯恩的总体成绩不佳<ref name="az-naval" />，他之后也表示学习这些课程让他非常吃力<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|134}}。在校期间，麦凯恩的外表邋遢、性格反叛，与所在连队军官的关系也不好，这都导致他在个人操守和领导能力上得分偏低，进一步影响总体成绩<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|41–42}}<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|130–131, 141–142}}。不过，这些并不妨碍他成为同学中人气颇高的领导者，用传记作家罗伯特·蒂姆伯格（{{lang|en|Robert Timberg}}）的话来说，麦凯恩是以“狂躁、直观而且非常奇特的方式”赢得同学的尊重<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}。麦凯恩颇为擅长吸引异性<ref name="az-naval" />，他经常同自称“坏蛋集团”的一群人合作组织不符学院规范的活动并因此在校园内小有名气<ref name="wapo083108" />，一位同学回忆称，“和约翰·麦凯恩一起恣意妄为，就仿佛置身火车失事现场”<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}，也有一些学子对他的做为感到恼怒<ref name="wapo083108" />。1957年6月，麦凯恩和其他同学登上[[弗莱彻级驱逐舰|弗莱彻级驱逐舰]]“[[亨特号驱逐舰|亨特号]]”（{{lang|en|USS Hunt}}）接受训练<ref>{{cite web|url=http://history.navy.mil/danfs/h9/hunt-ii.htm |title=Hunt |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728004604/http://www.history.navy.mil/danfs/h9/hunt-ii.htm |publisher=''Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships'' |date=2005-04-18 |accessdate=2016-01-10 |archivedate=2014-07-28 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>，结果表明他在舰艇军官技能方面有良好表现<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|135–138}}。乘舰抵达目的地[[里约热内卢|里约热内卢]]后，麦凯恩又同巴西时装模特兼芭蕾舞演员玛丽亚·格拉辛达（{{lang|en|Maria Gracinda}}）发展出梦幻般的浪漫恋情，之后两人还在圣诞节期间重聚<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|44–46}}<ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/brazilian-beauty-recalls-hot-rio-affair-young-john-mccain-article-1.324045 | title = Brazilian beauty recalls hot Rio affair with young John McCain | last1 = Emert | first1 = Harold | last2 = Sullivan | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150416000513/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/brazilian-beauty-recalls-hot-rio-affair-young-john-mccain-article-1.324045 | first2 = Patrick | publisher = ''New York Daily News'' | date = 2008-09-21 | accessdate = 2016-01-10 | archivedate = 2015-04-16 | deadurl = no}} In 2008, Maria Gracinda Teixeira de Jesus would remember the 50-year-old affair fondly and said that she never forgot McCain.</ref>。

1958年6月，麦凯恩从海军学院毕业，成绩在全部899名学生中排第894位<ref name="timberg-ns-ch1" />{{rp|31–35}}。虽然成绩不佳，但据麦凯恩之后回忆，他对勇气、韧性、荣誉和为国牺牲这些更加令人信服的传统并没有过任何抹黑之举，同时也始终没有放弃向家人证明，他也可以像家族中的海军先辈一样优秀<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|151–152}}。事实上，他的爸爸和爷爷和海军学院的成绩也不怎么样，毕业成绩分别是倒数第20名和倒数第3名<ref name="Timberg-1999" />{{rp|18, 28}}。麦凯恩之后才意识到自己在海军学院学习经历的宝贵，正是这段经历让他得以明白终生维持自尊的重要性，明白有些东西比自己的利益更加重要，10年之后，正是这些经历让他得以度过那段“绝望而摇摆不定”的时期<ref name="McCain-Salter-1999" />{{rp|151–152}}。

